Durban - A large police contingent has been deployed to stop the violence in Mtubatuba, north of the KZN, that erupted on Monday morning.

Pierre Conradie of Alpha security said about 20 police vehicles were at the scene this morning.

He said the violence looked to have started as a community service delivery protest and quickly got worse with trucks being the main target.

“The community stopped some of the trucks and looted the cargo, some of trucks had been tipped to the the ground others had been forced off the road and another had been burned,” he said.AdChoicesADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads







