He said one wood truck had lost part of its load on the road but that had  been partially cleared and the despite the damage and debri on the road, the road had been partially cleared.

“When I left there about around 9am this morning, traffic was able to move around and had started flowing.

RTI spokesperson Zinhle Mngomezulu said two trucks had been burned in what looked to have started out as a community protest.

The attacks on trucks come shortly after trucks were burned in the Mooi River toll plaza a few weeks ago. 
